Before attempting to run eclipse 3.0, I've been running eclipse 2.1.2.  Eclipse
2.1.2 was located in C:\Program Files\Eclipse, which I moved to C:\Program
Files\Eclipse-old and copied the new eclipse 3.0 into C:\Program Files\Eclipse.
 I've tried with eclipse 3.0 in a couple locations besides that, but keep
getting the same error.
*** Bug 69274 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Original summary: "Error has occurred"

It seems Eclipse does not work with AElfred2, which you probably have installed
under your <JRE_HOME>/lib/ext directory. Eclipse will run with Sun 1.4.1/1.4.2
built-in parser.

I believe this could be marked as a duplicate of bug 57298.
